DOCUMENT();

loadMacros("PG.pl", 
           "PGbasicmacros.pl",
           "PGanswermacros.pl",
           "PGstandard.pl",
           "extraAnswerEvaluators.pl", 
           "PGauxiliaryFunctions.pl", 
           "PGgraphmacros.pl", 
           "MathObjects.pl", 
           "PGchoicemacros.pl",
"parserPopUp.pl" 
          );

TEXT(beginproblem());

$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 0;

$ans1 = "b";
$ans3 = "a";

@sign = ("+","-");
$i = random(0,1,1);  # left =0  right = 1
$j = random(0,1,1);  # up = 0   down = 1

if ($i == 0) { $ans2 = "to the left of"; 
               $wrong2 = "to the right of";
               $exp2 = "left" }
        else { $ans2 = "to the right of";
               $wrong2 = "to the left of";
               $exp2 = "right" };

if ($j == 0) { $ans4 = "above"; 
               $wrong4 = "below";
               $exp4 = "up" }
        else { $ans4 = "below"; 
               $wrong4 = "above";
               $exp4 = "down" };

$popup1 = PopUp(["?","to the left of","to the right of"], $ans2);
$popup2 = PopUp(["?","above","below"], $ans4);


BEGIN_TEXT
Question 37:
$BR $SPACE $BR
Explain in words the effects of the transformations given in by the formula $BR
\( \ \ \ \ \ \ q(z $sign[$i] b) $sign[$j] a \) $BR
on the graph of \( q(z) \).   Assume $BITALIC a $EITALIC and $BITALIC b $EITALIC are positive constants.  For each shift, enter the parameter or number which identifies the amount of the shift, and then select the direction of the shift in the pulldown menus.
$BR $SPACE $BR


$BR $SPACE $BR
The graph of \( \ q(z $sign[$i] b) $sign[$j] a \ \) is \{ ans_rule(5) \} units \{ $popup1->menu() \} the graph of \( q(z) \), and \{ ans_rule(5) \} units \{ $popup2->menu() \} the graph of \( q(z) \).


END_TEXT

ANS(fun_cmp( $ans1, vars=>['a','b'] ) );
ANS($popup1->cmp() );
ANS(fun_cmp( $ans3, vars=>['a','b'] ) );
ANS($popup2->cmp() );


SOLUTION(EV3(<<'END_SOLUTION'));
$BR $SPACE $BR 
$BBOLD  SOLUTION $EBOLD
$BR 
From the inside change, we know that the graph is shifted $BITALIC b $EITALIC units to the $exp2.  From the outside change, we know that it is
shifted $BITALIC a $EITALIC units $exp4.  So, for any given $BITALIC z $EITALIC value, the graph of
\( q(z+b)-a \) is $BITALIC b $EITALIC units to the $exp2 and $BITALIC a $EITALIC units $ans4 the graph of \( q(z) \).
$BR
END_SOLUTION


COMMENT('MathObject version');
